The paper discusses a mechanism for detecting faulty sensors in IoT applications, which involves communication and computation resource management. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes the use of fog computing, which is a distributed computing paradigm, indicating that it could also belong to the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents performance analyses, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
